        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The “Mini Fish Feed Mills of Production Capacity of 2 Ton /Day” is a scheme component under the Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana (PMMSY), implemented by the Fisheries Department, Government of Haryana. This is a Centrally Sponsored Scheme, aims to strengthen inland aquaculture infrastructure by promoting the establishment of small-scale fish feed mills. Under this scheme, financial assistance, in form of subsidy, is provided to individuals for setting up mini feed mills, ensuring the local availability of quality fish feed at affordable prices for fishers and fish farmers.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "**Tangible Benefits:**\n\n- Project Cost: ₹30,00,000/- per unit\n- Subsidy will be limited to 40% of the project cost for General Category of beneficiaries.\n- Subsidy will be limited to 60% of the project cost for Weaker sections/ SC/ST/Women and their co-operatives of beneficiaries.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "Under this scheme, financial assistance, in form of subsidy, is provided to individuals for setting up mini feed mills, ensuring the local availability of quality fish feed at affordable prices for fishers and fish farmers.",
        "exclusions_md": "",
        "detailedDescription": [
